# Fix MetaMask, KYC Docs, Milestones & Donation Routes

## Summary of Investigation

After reviewing all backend routes, frontend pages, API config, and server setup, here are the findings:

### Issues Found

| # | Issue | Root Cause | Fix |
|---|-------|-----------|-----|
| 1 | **Admin can't confirm milestones** | Backend restricts to [hospital](file:///home/dungar/decentralizedCrowdFund/ai-service/main.py#702-753) role only (line 34 of [milestones.js](file:///home/dungar/decentralizedCrowdFund/backend/routes/milestones.js)). Frontend only shows button for [hospital](file:///home/dungar/decentralizedCrowdFund/ai-service/main.py#702-753) (line 504 of [CampaignDetail.tsx](file:///home/dungar/decentralizedCrowdFund/frontend/src/pages/CampaignDetail.tsx)). | Add `admin` to allowed roles in both backend and frontend. |
| 2 | **KYC documents not visible** | KYC route `GET /api/kyc/:id/documents/:docIndex` exists and looks correct (stores mimetype). Likely the URL path is working — need to verify in browser. If failing, it may be an encryption key issue. | Test in browser first. |
| 3 | **Donation backend-bypass insufficient funds** | `donate-direct` route uses the server's Hardhat account to send ETH. If that account ran out of ETH (100 ETH initial balance minus gas/donations), it fails with "insufficient funds". | This is expected — the Hardhat node needs funded accounts. Not a code bug. |
| 4 | **MetaMask donation fails** | The MetaMask flow works correctly — connects wallet, sends `donate()` to contract, backend verifies tx. If MetaMask has insufficient ETH, it will fail. | Not a bug — MetaMask needs ETH. The Hardhat node provides test accounts. |

### Routes Verified ✅

All backend routes are correctly registered in [server.js](file:///home/dungar/decentralizedCrowdFund/backend/server.js/home/dungar/decentralizedCrowdFund/backend/server.js):
- `/api/auth` → [auth.js](file:///home/dungar/decentralizedCrowdFund/backend/routes/auth.js) ✅
- `/api/campaigns` → [campaigns.js](file:///home/dungar/decentralizedCrowdFund/backend/routes/campaigns.js) ✅
- `/api/donations` → [donations.js](file:///home/dungar/decentralizedCrowdFund/backend/routes/donations.js) ✅
- `/api/milestones` → [milestones.js](file:///home/dungar/decentralizedCrowdFund/backend/routes/milestones.js) ✅
- `/api/admin` → [admin.js](file:///home/dungar/decentralizedCrowdFund/backend/routes/admin.js) ✅
- `/api/kyc` → [kyc.js](file:///home/dungar/decentralizedCrowdFund/backend/routes/kyc.js) ✅
- `/api/hospitals` → [hospitals.js](file:///home/dungar/decentralizedCrowdFund/backend/routes/hospitals.js) ✅
- `/api/analytics` → [analytics.js](file:///home/dungar/decentralizedCrowdFund/backend/routes/analytics.js) ✅
- `/api/transactions` → [transactions.js](file:///home/dungar/decentralizedCrowdFund/backend/routes/transactions.js) ✅

API interceptor in [api.ts](file:///home/dungar/decentralizedCrowdFund/frontend/src/services/api.ts) correctly strips `/api/` prefix from URLs and adds auth token.

