## Proposed Changes

### Milestone Confirmation

#### [MODIFY] [milestones.js](file:///home/dungar/decentralizedCrowdFund/backend/routes/milestones.js)

Add `admin` role to the milestone confirmation endpoint role check. When admin confirms, skip the hospital wallet verification since admin confirms off-chain via the backend-signed fallback.

```diff
- router.post('/:campaignId/confirm', authMiddleware, roleMiddleware(['hospital']), async (req, res) => {
+ router.post('/:campaignId/confirm', authMiddleware, roleMiddleware(['hospital', 'admin']), async (req, res) => {
```

Also skip the hospital ownership check when the caller is admin (admin should be able to confirm any campaign's milestones).

#### [MODIFY] [CampaignDetail.tsx](file:///home/dungar/decentralizedCrowdFund/frontend/src/pages/CampaignDetail.tsx)

Show milestone confirm buttons for both [hospital](file:///home/dungar/decentralizedCrowdFund/ai-service/main.py#702-753) and `admin` roles:

```diff
- {!isCompleted && campaign.status === "active" && user?.role === "hospital" && (
+ {!isCompleted && campaign.status === "active" && (user?.role === "hospital" || user?.role === "admin") && (
```

---

### KYC Document Viewer (Defensive Fix)

#### [MODIFY] [AdminKYCReview.tsx](file:///home/dungar/decentralizedCrowdFund/frontend/src/pages/AdminKYCReview.tsx)

The current code looks correct, but I'll add better error handling and a loading state for document opening to surface any hidden errors.

---

## User Review Required

> [!IMPORTANT]
> **Milestone confirm for admin**: Currently only hospitals can confirm milestones (by design — hospitals verify treatment completion). Should admins really be able to confirm milestones directly? This bypasses the hospital verification step. I'll add it since you requested it, but wanted to flag this.

> [!NOTE]
> **Donation MetaMask/balance issue**: The Hardhat node gives each test account 10,000 ETH. If you imported one of these accounts into MetaMask and configured the Hardhat network (Chain ID 31337, RPC http://127.0.0.1:8545), you'll have plenty of test ETH. The "backend bypass" donation uses the server's default Hardhat signer — if that ran out, restart `npx hardhat node` to reset balances.

## Verification Plan

### Browser Testing
1. Log in as admin → go to Campaign Detail page → verify milestone confirm buttons appear
2. Click confirm on a pending milestone → verify it works
3. Go to KYC Review → click a document → verify it opens correctly
4. Log in as donor → connect MetaMask → attempt a donation
5. Verify backend bypass donation works when contract is deployed

### Existing Tests
- Run `cd backend && npx jest tests/backend.test.js` — covers auth, campaigns, health, encryption
- Run `cd backend && npx jest tests/donations.test.js` — covers donation CRUD and refund flows
